declarations.description: Returns whether the element is hidden.

declarations.name: isDisabled
declarations.description: Returns whether the element is disabled.

declarations.name: isFocusable
declarations.description:
Determines whether an element is focusable.
Read more here: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/1599660/which-html-elements-can-receive-focus/1600194#1600194
Or here: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/18261595/how-to-check-if-a-dom-element-is-focusable

members.name: inactive
members.description: Determines whether the focus trap is active or not.

members.name: focused
members.description: Returns whether the element currently has focus.

members.name: focusFirstElement
members.description: Focuses the first focusable element in the focus trap.

members.name: focusLastElement
members.description: Focuses the last focusable element in the focus trap.

members.name: getFocusableElements
members.description: Returns a list of the focusable children found within the element.

members.name: trapFocus
members.description: Focuses on either the last or first focusable element.

members.name: onFocusIn
members.description: When the element gains focus this function is called.

members.name: onFocusOut
members.description: When the element looses its focus this function is called.

members.name: updateFocused
members.description:
Updates the focused property and updates the view.
The update is debounced because the focusin and focusout out
might fire multiple times in a row. We only want to render
the element once, therefore waiting until the focus is "stable".

attributes.name: inactive
attributes.description: Determines whether the focus trap is active or not.
